function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return lowercase(replace(strip(col), r"[\s-]+" => "_"))
end
```

This function `clean_column` takes in a string `col` that represents a column name. It first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces using `strip`, then it replaces any spaces or hyphens with an underscore using `replace` with a regular expression `r"[\s-]+"` that matches one or more occurrences of spaces or hyphens. Finally, it converts the string to lowercase using `lowercase`.
